programme.desc: Steve and Stan, who don't have much in common, try to bond on a road trip to Albuquerque in search of a pair of the distinctive DeLorean doors to complete a car that Stan has been building. Meanwhile, Roger, Hayley and Francine decide to have an adventure of their own, but they can't decide what to do.

programme.title: American Dad!
programme.desc: Steve joins a football team to please Stan, who then takes over as coach and gives Steve the boot because he isn't good enough. Meanwhile, Francine and Hayley vie for a blue ribbon at the county fair. Guest voices include Will Forte (Mayor Woodside) and Liz Torres (Councilwoman Santos).

programme.title: American Dad!
programme.desc: Roger declares that he was sent to Earth to be "the decider" of humanity's fate, and Stan challenges him on it. Guest voices include Sandra Oh, Bob Odenkirk, Joss Stone, Grace Park of "Battlestar Galactica", Glenn Howerton of "It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia" and Geico caveman John Lehr.

programme.title: Hang 'em High
programme.desc: A rancher survives a vicious attack by a lynch mob who accused him of stealing cattle, and he sets out for revenge by becoming a deputy marshal and agreeing to bring in alive the men he is looking for so they can face trials.

programme.title: The Unforgiven
programme.desc: A white family in the Texas panhandle is at the center of controversy because they have an adopted Kiowa child, and there is a great amount of tension in the town between those two races. When the secret goes public, a war begins.

programme.title: Bird of Paradise
programme.desc: A beautiful Polynesian woman falls in love just after electing to sacrifice herself to a volcano god.

programme.title: The Good Earth
programme.desc: As the devoted wife of a farmer who goes from extreme poverty to great wealth, Luise Rainer won the Best Actress Oscar (her second in a row) in this adaptation of Pearl S. Buck's Pulitzer Prize-winning novel about rural China in the early 1900s. The film, which was nominated for Best Picture, was producer Irving Thalberg's final one. Karl Freund's cinematography also took home an Oscar.

programme.title: Cage of Evil
programme.desc: Jewel thievery and a corrupt police detective. Ron Foster. Holly: Pat Blair. Kearns: Harp McGuire. Colton: Preston Hanson. Melrose: John Maxwell. Barney: Doug Henderson. Directed by Edward L. Cahn.

programme.title: The Toast of New York
programme.desc: A rowdy robber baron financier of the 1880s sets his sights on cornering the gold market, as well as the affection of a gorgeous, young actress.

programme.title: A Stolen Life
programme.desc: A good woman pines for a man who falls in love with her identical sister, who is the black sheep of the family. Bette Davis plays the sisters.

programme.title: Who's Afraid of Virginia Woolf?
programme.desc: Edward Albee's scathing study of a turbulent marriage has as its ground zero the New England home of a middle-aged college professor and his wife, who serve much more than a nightcap to the young faculty couple they host. Winner of five Academy Awards, including Best Actress (Elizabeth Taylor) and Best Supporting Actress (Sandy Dennis).

programme.title: Dodsworth
programme.desc: Best Picture nominee is an adaptation of the Sinclair Lewis novel about a rich couple's marriage unraveling during a grand tour of Europe, where she takes up with a minor member of royalty and he falls for an attractive widow.

programme.title: To Yuma
programme.desc: Dan Evans, a small time farmer, is hired to escort Ben Wade, a dangerous outlaw, to Yuma. As Evans and Wade wait for the 3:10 train to Yuma, Wade's gang is racing to free him.

programme.title: Get Shorty
programme.desc: A collector for the mob travels to L.A. to get a payment from a Hollywood producer, and discovers his skills in the world of organized crime translate to the movie business in this showbiz comedy. After helping a producer land a big-name actor for a script, he also helps the compromised man get out of a relationship with a powerful drug dealer.

programme.title: Where Are My Children?
programme.desc: This controversial silent drama about birth control centers on a wealthy district attorney's wife who visits an abortion doctor on a number of occasions to avoid bearing children.

programme.title: The Cars That Ate Paris
programme.desc: No, it's not about carnivorous cars chowing down on Frenchmen, but a horror comedy set in Paris, Australia, where the chief source of income is selling the salvage remaining from orchestrated automobile accidents. Those who survive the crashes are usually subjected to bizarre brain experiments by the local mad scientist.

programme.title: The Plumber
programme.desc: A mysterious plumber moves in with a married couple, and his bizarre behavior challenges the wife's perception of her own life so strongly that when he finally leaves she's left a paranoid mess.

programme.title: Musical Movieland
programme.desc: Tourists are shown around film studios where several well-known movie musicals were shot.

programme.title: Uncertain Glory
programme.desc: A detective's pursuit of a criminal takes a grimly ironic twist in Nazi-occupied France when the hood is given the chance to redeem himself by posing as a resistance leader who can save the lives of innocent villagers if he surrenders to the Germans.

programme.title: Nazi Agent
programme.desc: An American-loving German impersonates his Nazi twin and attempts to thwart their plans to sabotage Allied shipping routes.

programme.title: Desperate Journey
programme.desc: World War II escape saga about five survivors of a downed RAF bomber trying to make it out of Germany.

programme.title: 2001: A Space Odyssey

Altschul: Marius Goring. Hirsch: Anton Diffring. Von Gorian: Andrew Keir. Whiteney: Rupert Davies. Stephanie: Alexandra Stewart. Etienne Perier directed.

programme.title: Brainstorm
programme.desc: A research scientist experiments with a revolutionary brain-reading device that is able to translate a person's thoughts to videotape, but soon finds himself at odds with the government. The film was Natalie Wood's last screen appearance.

programme.title: The Little Girl Who Lives Down the Lane
programme.desc: A teenage girl attempts to keep a secret from everyone in order to preserve her independent lifestyle. A nosy neighbor and a neighborhood pedophile threaten her goal.

programme.title: Spider Baby
